# Line-ending policy
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Force LF for ALL text in the repo and in the working tree, regardless of
# the local `core.autocrlf` setting. Reason: tools that hash file content
# (forge fmt --check on *.sol, dotnet format on *.cs, rustfmt, prettier)
# treat CRLF as a diff against the LF that's actually committed, producing
# false "format drift" failures on Windows/WSL2 checkouts where autocrlf
# converts on the way out. Pinning eol=lf here neutralizes that.
#
# `text=auto` detects text vs binary on first commit; `eol=lf` overrides
# any user-side autocrlf for everything matched. Per-extension lines below
# are explicit pins for source we know is text — they short-circuit the
# auto-detection and survive future tools that ignore `text=auto`.

* text=auto eol=lf

# ─── C# / .NET ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.cs            text eol=lf
*.csproj        text eol=lf
*.props         text eol=lf
*.targets       text eol=lf
*.sln           text eol=lf
*.runsettings   text eol=lf
*.editorconfig  text eol=lf
*.config        text eol=lf

# ─── Rust ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.rs            text eol=lf
*.toml          text eol=lf
Cargo.lock      text eol=lf

# ─── TypeScript / JavaScript ───────────────────────────────────────
*.ts            text eol=lf
*.tsx           text eol=lf
*.js            text eol=lf
*.mjs           text eol=lf
*.cjs           text eol=lf
*.jsx           text eol=lf
package.json    text eol=lf
package-lock.json text eol=lf

# ─── Solidity (Foundry) — the trigger case for this file ───────────
*.sol           text eol=lf

# ─── Solana / Anchor ───────────────────────────────────────────────
Anchor.toml     text eol=lf

# ─── Config + docs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.json          text eol=lf
*.json5         text eol=lf
*.yml           text eol=lf
*.yaml          text eol=lf
*.md            text eol=lf
*.txt           text eol=lf
*.html          text eol=lf
*.css           text eol=lf
*.svg           text eol=lf

# ─── Shell scripts MUST be LF (CRLF breaks #!/bin/sh on Linux) ─────
*.sh            text eol=lf
*.bash          text eol=lf
*.fish          text eol=lf

# ─── Python / Go / Proto (if anything lands later) ─────────────────
*.py            text eol=lf
*.go            text eol=lf
*.proto         text eol=lf

# ─── Windows-only batch files keep CRLF ────────────────────────────
*.bat           text eol=crlf
*.cmd           text eol=crlf
*.ps1           text eol=crlf

# ─── Binary files — never touch ────────────────────────────────────
*.png           binary
*.jpg           binary
*.jpeg          binary
*.gif           binary
*.ico           binary
*.pdf           binary
*.zip           binary
*.gz            binary
*.bz2           binary
*.xz            binary
*.7z            binary
*.tar           binary
*.exe           binary
*.dll           binary
*.so            binary
*.dylib         binary
*.bin           binary
*.wasm          binary
*.nef           binary
*.woff          binary
*.woff2         binary
*.ttf           binary
*.otf           binary
*.eot           binary
*.mp3           binary
*.mp4           binary
*.mov           binary
*.wav           binary
